DTEND:20260710T080000
SUMMARY:LinkedIn POST — P2: Quarantine vs disable a flaky test
DESCRIPTION:Draft this post before Thursday.\nAngle: most teams disable and call it quarantine. quarantine means: isolated, tracked, owner assigned, deadline to fix or delete.\n\nSee content-plan.md — Week 2 Thursday.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:linkedin-post-w2-fri@sdet-content
DTSTART:20260711T073000
DTEND:20260711T080000
SUMMARY:LinkedIn POST — CONTRARIAN: your e2e tests are not the problem
DESCRIPTION:Draft this post before Friday.\nAngle: everyone blames e2e tests for being slow and flaky. the tests are showing you the truth about the app. you're blaming the messenger.\n\nSee content-plan.md — Week 2 Friday.
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:linkedin-weekly-review@sdet-content
DTSTART:20260703T170000
DTEND:20260703T171500
SUMMARY:LinkedIn weekly review (10 min)
DESCRIPTION:Every Friday — 10 minutes:\n1. Follower count delta vs last week\n2. Which post got the most comments? why?\n3. Which comment brought the most profile visits?\n4. One thing to do more of next week\n5. One thing to cut\n\nUpdate content-plan.md status column.
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=FR
END:VEVENT

BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:linkedin-daily-comments@sdet-content
DTSTART:20260630T083000
DTEND:20260630T090000
SUMMARY:LinkedIn — 5-10 comments on Playwright/QA posts
DESCRIPTION:Daily habit — 30 min max:\n\nSearch: Playwright / test automation / flaky tests / AI testing\nFilter: Past 24 hours — sort by Top\nTarget: posts with 50+ likes\n\nQuality bar: add a specific detail not in the post. name the tool or number. end with a practitioner question.\n\nUse linkedin-comment-drafter for Tier 1 posts.
RRULE:FREQ=WEEKLY;BYDAY=MO,TU,WE,TH,FR
